
README file for ERC32 cross-compilation system (erc32ccs-2.0)
-------------------------------------------------------------

1. Introduction

The erc32ccs is a cross-compilation system that consists of the following:

- GNU c/c++ compiler (egcs-1.1.1)
- GNAT Ada95 compiler (gnat-3.11p)
- Linker, assembler, archiver etc. (binutils-2.9.1)
- RTEMS real-time kernel (rtems-4.0.0)
- Standalone C-library (newlib-1.8.1 from Cygnus)
- Standalone ERC32 simulator (sis-3.0.2)
- GNU debugger with ERC32 simulator (gdb-4.17 + sis-3.0.2 + gnat patch)
- Graphic user interace for gdb (ddd-3.1.3)

With erc32ccs, is possible compile and link ERC32 programs, and to
run them on the ERC32 simulator or a remote target. Using the debugger, 
it is also possible to perform source-level symbolic debugging.

